      <div xml:id="Sonnet41">
        <interpGrp type="poembox">
          <interp ana="#form" type="narrative"/>
          <interp ana="#tone" type="love"/>
          <interp ana="#topic" type="nature"/>
        </interpGrp>
        <lg>
          <l>You are a nobody</l>
          <l>until another man leaves</l>
          <l>a note under your wiper:</l>
          <l>I like your hair, clothes, car-call me!</l>                                      
          <l>Late May, i brush pink</l>
          <l>Crepe Myrtle blossoms</l>
          <l>from the hood of my car.</l>
          <l>Again spring factors</l>
          <l>into our fever. Would this</l>
          <l>affair leave any room for error?</l>
          <l>What if i only want</l>
          <l>him to hum me a lullably.</l>
          <l>To rest in the nets</l>
          <l>of our own preferences.</l>
          <l>I think of women</l>
          <l>I've loved who, near the end,</l>
          <l>made love to me soley</l>
          <l>for the endorphines. Praise</l>
          <l>be to those bodies lit</l>
          <l>with magic. I pulse</l>
          <l>my wipers, sweep away pollen</l>
          <l>from the windsheild glass</l>
          <l>to allow the radar</l>
          <l>dector to detect. In the prim</l>
          <l>light of spring I drive</l>
          <l>home alone along the river's</l>
          <l>tight curves where it bends</l>
          <l>like handwritten words.</l>
          <l>On the radio, a foreign love</l>
          <l>song some men sing to rise.</l>
          
          
